sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Startup Folder File Write
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: A General detection for files being created in the Windows startup directory. This could be an indicator of persistence.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Roberto Rodriguez (Cyb3rWard0g), OTR (Open Threat Research)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Potentially Suspicious CMD Shell Output Redirect
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects inline Windows shell commands redirecting output via the ">" symbol to a suspicious location.
This technique is sometimes used by malicious actors in order to redirect the output of reconnaissance commands such as "hostname" and "dir" to files for future exfiltration.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Startup Folder File Write

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Non Interactive PowerShell Process Spawned
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Roberto Rodriguez @Cyb3rWard0g (rule), oscd.community (improvements)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: ADS Zone.Identifier Deleted By Uncommon Application
